00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:42,355 --> 00:00:43,273
Ju-ran.

2
00:00:44,524 --> 00:00:46,442
Can you hear your Dad's voice now?

3
00:00:48,278 --> 00:00:50,488
<i>It was the first thing I ever heard.</i>

4
00:00:51,072 --> 00:00:52,782
<i>The sound of warmth.</i>

5
00:01:22,228 --> 00:01:23,688
<i>But the fairy tale</i>

6
00:01:24,814 --> 00:01:27,025
<i>did not have a happy ending.</i>

7
00:01:33,072 --> 00:01:34,616
Help! Over here!

8
00:01:34,699 --> 00:01:36,576
Father!

9
00:01:36,659 --> 00:01:39,370
Father!

10
00:02:09,067 --> 00:02:10,193
Run away.

11
00:02:10,276 --> 00:02:11,486
You have to run, Ju-ran.

12
00:02:11,569 --> 00:02:14,197
I <i>will </i>come and find you, so until then,

13
00:02:14,739 --> 00:02:17,408
keep yourself hidden
and don't get caught, okay?

14
00:02:21,204 --> 00:02:23,039
Go!

15
00:02:36,177 --> 00:02:37,095
Let's go.

16
00:02:39,555 --> 00:02:42,475
<i>The children decided</i>
<i>to keep their identities secret</i>

17
00:02:42,558 --> 00:02:44,978
<i>and live in hiding,</i>

18
00:02:45,561 --> 00:02:47,689
<i>waiting for their father</i>
<i>to keep his promise</i>

19
00:02:48,189 --> 00:02:50,441
<i>and return to them.</i>

20
00:02:53,444 --> 00:02:55,446
If you're deaf,
you should at least be sharp.

21
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:58,199
If you're not sharp,
you could at least be handy.

22
00:02:58,283 --> 00:03:00,159
What a pain!

23
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,998
Ju-ran.

24
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,678
It's me, Dad.

25
00:03:20,805 --> 00:03:24,142
<i>But the fairy tale did not end there.</i>

26
00:04:02,096 --> 00:04:03,639
Will that be enough?

27
00:04:03,723 --> 00:04:05,850
We have to start somewhere.

28
00:04:07,769 --> 00:04:09,896
You kids focus on
finding the Child of Eternity.

29
00:04:11,898 --> 00:04:14,108
That's the only thing
that will get us closer

30
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:16,319
to a cure for the side effects.

31
00:04:17,653 --> 00:04:19,530
<i>The children realized</i>

32
00:04:20,573 --> 00:04:23,409
<i>that only by finding</i>
<i>the child with the heart of eternity</i>

33
00:04:24,077 --> 00:04:25,828
<i>could all of this</i>

34
00:04:26,412 --> 00:04:29,248
<i>reach a happy ending.</i>

35
00:04:33,836 --> 00:04:36,381
I heard you were released on parole.

36
00:04:37,131 --> 00:04:38,758
A year ago, I believe.

37
00:04:39,425 --> 00:04:42,845
I was in there for over 20 years.

38
00:04:43,971 --> 00:04:46,808
I'm sure it was
hardly enough time to recall

39
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:49,102
the faces of all the dead children.

40
00:04:49,185 --> 00:04:52,146
You never even cared about them
in the first place.

41
00:04:53,648 --> 00:04:55,942
Whatever happened to those children,

42
00:04:56,025 --> 00:04:59,529
abandoned, abused,
and wandering listlessly…

43
00:05:00,321 --> 00:05:01,197
You never cared.

44
00:05:02,865 --> 00:05:05,493
My children and I risked everything

45
00:05:05,576 --> 00:05:08,788
for that immortality project of yours.

46
00:05:09,288 --> 00:05:12,458
And though, yes,
some sacrifices were made,

47
00:05:13,209 --> 00:05:14,377
I was successful.

48
00:05:16,170 --> 00:05:19,590
And yet, to be treated as I was,
like a criminal…

49
00:05:21,259 --> 00:05:22,552
I must say, I was hurt.

50
00:05:23,386 --> 00:05:24,595
It seems that one of us

51
00:05:25,221 --> 00:05:27,682
has been laboring
under a grave misunderstanding.

52
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:31,727
I didn't fund and support you

53
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,397
because I wanted you to succeed.

54
00:05:34,939 --> 00:05:36,649
It was for the suffering children.

55
00:05:38,067 --> 00:05:40,987
I wonder if believing that
eases your conscience.

56
00:05:45,616 --> 00:05:47,702
I heard that you, Madam King,

57
00:05:48,202 --> 00:05:50,538
took in most of the rescued children.

58
00:05:50,621 --> 00:05:53,124
I found every one of them new families

59
00:05:53,749 --> 00:05:55,626
or sent them to study abroad.

60
00:05:55,710 --> 00:05:56,544
Why do you ask?

61
00:05:57,879 --> 00:05:59,088
And the Child of Eternity?

62
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,637
So you've seen the Child of Eternity.

63
00:06:09,182 --> 00:06:10,266
Where is that child?

64
00:06:50,181 --> 00:06:51,891
Let me ask you again.

65
00:06:52,391 --> 00:06:55,144
Where is the Child of Eternity now?

66
00:06:57,688 --> 00:07:01,567
Director Choi already told me everything
with his last breath.

67
00:07:02,527 --> 00:07:05,821
That only you, Madam King of Hearty House,

68
00:07:06,656 --> 00:07:08,491
know where the Child of Eternity is.

69
00:07:09,825 --> 00:07:11,160
Answer him.

70
00:07:19,085 --> 00:07:19,919
That child…

71
00:07:26,342 --> 00:07:27,426
is dead.

72
00:07:32,348 --> 00:07:33,266
What did you say?

73
00:07:35,101 --> 00:07:36,644
Dead.

74
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:42,316
<i>The Child of Eternity cannot die.</i>

75
00:07:53,536 --> 00:07:56,289
-One more time.
-No, please. Stop.

76
00:07:56,372 --> 00:07:58,583
-It's okay.
-I'm scared.

77
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:01,294
-Please stop.
-Stop it.

78
00:08:01,377 --> 00:08:03,045
No, please stop. I'm scared.

79
00:08:03,129 --> 00:08:04,589
Can't you hear me?

80
00:08:04,672 --> 00:08:07,133
-I'm scared. Please, no.
-Hurry.

81
00:08:07,216 --> 00:08:09,927
Please stop. No.

82
00:08:10,011 --> 00:08:11,554
Stop it.

83
00:08:12,805 --> 00:08:14,348
<i>But immortality doesn't mean</i>

84
00:08:15,558 --> 00:08:17,184
<i>immunity to pain.</i>

85
00:08:19,186 --> 00:08:20,396
<i>Every moment,</i>

86
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:23,566
<i>with each and every death.</i>

87
00:08:33,951 --> 00:08:35,119
One more time!

88
00:08:35,202 --> 00:08:37,079
-No, I'm scared!
-It's okay.

89
00:08:37,163 --> 00:08:38,706
Please stop!

90
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,124
I said stop!

91
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,543
-Stop it!
-Don't do this.

92
00:08:46,881 --> 00:08:48,799
-Please don't do this.
-One more time!

93
00:08:48,883 --> 00:08:50,718
Stop!

94
00:08:53,095 --> 00:08:54,972
I told you to stop.

95
00:08:55,056 --> 00:08:56,098
Stop!

96
00:08:57,433 --> 00:08:58,684
Stop it!

97
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:01,020
Just stop it!

98
00:09:34,136 --> 00:09:37,139
Ma'am, how much rice should we use?

99
00:09:40,685 --> 00:09:41,769
Rice.

100
00:09:41,852 --> 00:09:44,563
How much should we soak
for the celebratory rice cakes?

101
00:09:44,647 --> 00:09:45,815
Right.

102
00:09:46,607 --> 00:09:48,901
You should soak about three to five <i>mal</i>.

103
00:09:48,984 --> 00:09:51,070
So how much exactly?

104
00:09:51,153 --> 00:09:53,197
Three <i>mal </i>or four <i>mal</i>?

105
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,240
Or five <i>mal</i>?

106
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:58,828
Goodness, what's gotten into you?
You're usually so precise.

107
00:09:59,829 --> 00:10:01,163
Hey, Won-ju.

108
00:10:02,164 --> 00:10:02,998
Yes?

109
00:10:03,082 --> 00:10:05,376
Didn't someone come by just now?

110
00:10:05,459 --> 00:10:07,378
Who would've come by?

111
00:10:07,461 --> 00:10:09,380
You've been sitting alone the whole time.

112
00:10:09,964 --> 00:10:11,382
And how much red bean?

113
00:10:11,882 --> 00:10:13,592
Three to five <i>mal </i>of that too?

114
00:10:13,676 --> 00:10:15,469
What on earth happened here?

115
00:10:15,553 --> 00:10:16,387
Goodness me.

116
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:18,848
Was there an earthquake or something?

117
00:10:18,931 --> 00:10:21,892
Goodness, how completely bizarre.

118
00:10:21,976 --> 00:10:25,354
They say the apocalypse is coming.
Maybe the world really is about to end.

119
00:10:25,438 --> 00:10:27,064
Or maybe someone upset the spirits?

120
00:10:27,148 --> 00:10:30,192
Why are all these
strange things happening?

121
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:12,735
Pretty.

122
00:11:13,944 --> 00:11:15,946
Should I go to see the Northern Lights?

123
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,698
I heard they're breathtaking.

124
00:11:18,532 --> 00:11:19,450
Hold up.

125
00:11:20,534 --> 00:11:22,953
Couldn't I just teleport there?

126
00:11:23,871 --> 00:11:24,789
No way.

127
00:11:25,456 --> 00:11:27,458
Does that mean I can save on airfares?

128
00:11:28,709 --> 00:11:30,669
Hey, that's pretty awesome!

129
00:11:31,712 --> 00:11:32,922
Pretty darn awesome!

130
00:11:43,891 --> 00:11:45,267
ABILITY: GRAVITY
RANK: S

131
00:11:47,645 --> 00:11:49,480
ABILITY: HALLUCINATION
GRADE: S

132
00:11:51,941 --> 00:11:54,151
ABILITY: BRAINWASHING
RANK: S

133
00:12:48,497 --> 00:12:52,209
THE WONDERFOOLS

134
00:12:53,419 --> 00:12:58,090
EPISODE 4
BOON THE KING DUCK VS WUNDERKINDER

135
00:13:22,489 --> 00:13:23,991
Hey, I used to use that thing.

136
00:13:24,074 --> 00:13:27,202
I heard retro is in these days.
Are you into it too?

137
00:13:27,286 --> 00:13:30,289
My CD player broke,
and apparently, it's beyond repair.

138
00:13:31,373 --> 00:13:34,585
Mom says I should save for a new one,
but it'll take forever.

139
00:13:34,668 --> 00:13:35,586
Hey, wait.

140
00:13:38,172 --> 00:13:40,299
How about I get you one for your birthday?

141
00:13:40,883 --> 00:13:42,176
For which birthday?

142
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:45,512
With your allowance,
I'd have to wait until I'm 40 to get it.

143
00:13:47,514 --> 00:13:48,599
Hey, your lunchbox.

144
00:13:58,025 --> 00:13:59,360
Have a good day, sweetie.

145
00:14:07,534 --> 00:14:09,578
How's this thing broken exactly?

146
00:14:17,628 --> 00:14:19,505
Thousand, ten thousand, hundred thousand…

147
00:14:21,882 --> 00:14:24,593
At this price, I couldn't afford it
by her 60th birthday,

148
00:14:25,094 --> 00:14:26,553
let alone her 40th.

149
00:14:33,227 --> 00:14:35,938
Cheong, you overestimate your old man.

150
00:14:42,111 --> 00:14:42,945
Hello?

151
00:14:44,154 --> 00:14:46,156
What do you want, Lady Trainwreck?

152
00:14:46,907 --> 00:14:49,743
Let's go home, shall we?
Mr. Coo-coo, let's go home.

153
00:14:49,827 --> 00:14:52,830
Let's go home. Back to your happy home.

154
00:14:52,913 --> 00:14:55,249
Come on, now. Let's go.

155
00:14:56,125 --> 00:14:57,751
Let's go.

156
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:10,347
<i>Master!</i>

157
00:15:33,037 --> 00:15:34,163
Why are you all…

158
00:15:34,246 --> 00:15:37,124
You asked if we were free on Friday.
And they both were.

159
00:15:37,207 --> 00:15:38,167
All right.

160
00:15:38,834 --> 00:15:41,754
How does it feel to have the calvary
on your team, Master?

161
00:15:41,837 --> 00:15:45,132
Calvary is where Jesus was crucified.
You mean the cavalry.

162
00:15:45,215 --> 00:15:46,717
Get off me.

163
00:15:47,968 --> 00:15:52,222
I must say, you're smarter
than I thought, Mr. Oddball.

164
00:15:52,306 --> 00:15:56,602
Who knew you'd give us special training
disguised as Civil Complaints Office work?

165
00:15:57,186 --> 00:15:58,854
We'll be paid for this, right?

166
00:15:59,688 --> 00:16:00,564
Special training?

167
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:03,400
You were totally rad.

168
00:16:03,901 --> 00:16:06,779
Lifting things, not to mention my heart,
up and down with one finger!

169
00:16:06,862 --> 00:16:08,197
It was totally--

170
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,156
What are you doing?

171
00:16:09,948 --> 00:16:12,576
As for me,
my heart was brimming with excitement.

172
00:16:12,659 --> 00:16:16,371
Like I've become a real civil servant.
And now, you're offering to teach us.

173
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:19,374
Does this mean
we can become as cool as you, Master?

174
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:21,585
Thank you so much!

175
00:16:21,668 --> 00:16:23,378
I will never forget this kindness!

176
00:16:23,462 --> 00:16:24,505
You kiss-ass.

177
00:16:24,588 --> 00:16:27,633
Mr. Lee Un-jeong. Very good!
You've finally put together a team?

178
00:16:27,716 --> 00:16:29,468
-Two, three!
-Hello!

179
00:16:29,551 --> 00:16:32,638
We're Team Lee Un-jeong
from the Haeseong Civil Complaints Office!

180
00:16:32,721 --> 00:16:34,223
At your service!

181
00:16:37,226 --> 00:16:38,060
Are you for real?

182
00:16:39,937 --> 00:16:40,979
Yes, well…

183
00:16:41,063 --> 00:16:44,316
Now, Mr. Lee Un-jeong here
has many shortcomings,

184
00:16:44,399 --> 00:16:46,527
so I'm sure you must be worried, Mr. Yang.

185
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:47,653
But

186
00:16:48,195 --> 00:16:49,446
he's got us now, see?

187
00:16:51,323 --> 00:16:55,744
We'll make up for all of his shortcomings,
so don't you worry.

188
00:16:55,828 --> 00:16:56,662
Sure.

189
00:16:57,454 --> 00:17:00,707
Well, then, before my worries
get the better of me…

190
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:02,042
Bring it in.

191
00:17:02,543 --> 00:17:03,877
Let's do this. Good.

192
00:17:06,255 --> 00:17:07,422
I'll see you later!

193
00:17:07,506 --> 00:17:08,882
Don't you worry!

194
00:17:10,592 --> 00:17:12,803
What's that? The bus? Over here, everyone.

195
00:17:12,886 --> 00:17:14,429
Careful. Watch out for the bus.

196
00:17:14,513 --> 00:17:17,182
Okay, keep it coming.

197
00:17:17,266 --> 00:17:19,309
Keep coming. That's it.

198
00:17:21,478 --> 00:17:23,605
Stop!

199
00:17:23,689 --> 00:17:24,523
All right.

200
00:17:25,023 --> 00:17:26,483
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

201
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:29,903
Why is the Church
of Eternal Salvation here?

202
00:17:30,487 --> 00:17:33,198
-Why are those cultists here?
-Must be here to recruit us.

203
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,202
Special orders from the mayor,
so no grumbling, okay?

204
00:17:37,286 --> 00:17:40,998
Any unnecessary complaining,
and all contract staff could be let go.

205
00:17:41,874 --> 00:17:44,334
Why, yes. There you are. Hello.

206
00:17:44,418 --> 00:17:45,294
All right.

207
00:17:45,377 --> 00:17:47,921
Today is our street clean-up drive,

208
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:51,758
and members of the Church
of Eternal Salvation will be helping us.

209
00:17:51,842 --> 00:17:54,011
Let's welcome them
with a round of applause!

210
00:17:54,094 --> 00:17:55,596
Let's give them a hand!

211
00:17:55,679 --> 00:17:58,599
-Welcome, all! Yes!
-My goodness.

212
00:17:59,558 --> 00:18:02,144
Thank you for the warm welcome.

213
00:18:03,187 --> 00:18:07,149
When it comes to cleaning up Haeseong,
of course we should help out.

214
00:18:09,151 --> 00:18:11,278
Trash should be collected immediately

215
00:18:11,361 --> 00:18:14,156
to make the world
a clean and beautiful place.

216
00:18:14,239 --> 00:18:16,742
Yes, you're absolutely right.

217
00:18:16,825 --> 00:18:17,659
<i>Collecting?</i>

218
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:20,704
To cleanse the world
and make it beautiful.

219
00:18:23,373 --> 00:18:25,209
Can we talk for a moment?

220
00:18:27,211 --> 00:18:28,045
Come on.

221
00:18:29,046 --> 00:18:31,340
Man, he's got us running
all over the place.

222
00:18:35,385 --> 00:18:36,511
Why are we here?

223
00:18:41,225 --> 00:18:43,894
The work's just a front
for us to train here, isn't it?

224
00:18:43,977 --> 00:18:45,604
Of course.

225
00:18:45,687 --> 00:18:48,106
We can't do our special training
out in the open.

226
00:18:48,190 --> 00:18:49,358
We have to be discreet.

227
00:18:50,943 --> 00:18:52,069
No special training.

228
00:18:52,152 --> 00:18:53,946
-Are you kidding?
-What?

229
00:18:55,906 --> 00:18:58,992
People only envy and admire people
with abilities like ours

230
00:18:59,493 --> 00:19:00,494
in movies.

231
00:19:01,328 --> 00:19:03,830
People fear and avoid
those who are different.

232
00:19:04,331 --> 00:19:06,458
They are shunned and despised.

233
00:19:06,541 --> 00:19:09,586
People already fear and avoid
Lady Trainwreck here.

234
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:12,756
Should I show you why
right here, right now?

235
00:19:19,513 --> 00:19:20,555
This is it.

236
00:19:22,724 --> 00:19:25,686
To live normal lives,
you must control and hide your abilities.

237
00:19:26,353 --> 00:19:27,771
If someone finds out

238
00:19:28,605 --> 00:19:31,233
and if that someone
is very intrigued by your abilities,

239
00:19:33,443 --> 00:19:34,569
you might never

240
00:19:35,195 --> 00:19:36,071
get to see…

241
00:19:38,073 --> 00:19:41,702
your friends, family,
or those you cherish ever again.

242
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:50,877
So we'd really get carted off
if we're caught?

243
00:19:51,670 --> 00:19:53,380
Never get to see them again?

244
00:19:54,131 --> 00:19:56,133
No special training would suffice.

245
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:58,719
Everyone's abilities manifest differently,

246
00:19:58,802 --> 00:20:01,054
so you have to figure out
your own abilities.

247
00:20:01,138 --> 00:20:05,350
And how exactly do we figure that out?
That's what we've been asking you.

248
00:20:05,434 --> 00:20:06,435
Repetition.

249
00:20:07,602 --> 00:20:11,732
The only option is repeated practice.
There will be some kind of rule.

250
00:20:12,232 --> 00:20:15,235
Focus on when and in what situations
your abilities manifest.

251
00:20:16,862 --> 00:20:20,699
No one leaves this place today
until they've figured something out.

252
00:20:22,326 --> 00:20:24,995
Like a fiery test by fire.

253
00:20:25,078 --> 00:20:26,246
<i>Trial </i>by fire.

254
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:28,999
Isn't that a bit too hardcore,
Mr. Oddball?

255
00:20:29,082 --> 00:20:30,751
Can't you go easy on us?

256
00:20:31,251 --> 00:20:33,879
You're not going to lock us up in here

257
00:20:33,962 --> 00:20:36,089
and ship us off in this container,
are you?

258
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:38,675
Come on, who would buy
a shipping container full of us?

259
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:41,219
He's just pushing us so we learn faster.

260
00:20:41,303 --> 00:20:43,638
Understood.
I'll do my best to learn, Master.

261
00:20:43,722 --> 00:20:44,931
Is that what you're doing?

262
00:20:47,601 --> 00:20:49,227
Lock the door from the outside.

263
00:20:49,311 --> 00:20:52,064
-Okay! Let's give it a try.
-Wait, the door?

264
00:20:52,147 --> 00:20:53,065
Let's do this!

265
00:20:53,148 --> 00:20:55,901
Is locking the door really necessary?

266
00:21:00,113 --> 00:21:01,281
This isn't too shabby.

267
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:06,995
Let's take one of each.

268
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,789
You punk, can't you see I'm hurt?

269
00:21:14,169 --> 00:21:16,630
<i>So we saved them?</i>

270
00:21:20,342 --> 00:21:23,845
We're pretty awesome,

271
00:21:23,929 --> 00:21:25,472
aren't we?

272
00:21:30,852 --> 00:21:31,728
<i>No.</i>

273
00:21:32,229 --> 00:21:33,855
<i>That's not me.</i>

274
00:21:34,815 --> 00:21:35,899
<i>I'm just…</i>

275
00:21:41,029 --> 00:21:42,030
Dr. Ha.

276
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:55,460
His vitals are also declining.

277
00:22:01,091 --> 00:22:02,300
Scrap him.

278
00:22:13,937 --> 00:22:16,106
We won't end up like that
one day, will we?

279
00:22:19,860 --> 00:22:21,570
If we can't fix the side effects,

280
00:22:22,404 --> 00:22:24,072
we could get deformed like that too.

281
00:22:25,615 --> 00:22:28,827
I just wonder if we'll end up
gasping for air, unable to breathe,

282
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:31,455
and ultimately scrapped, just like them.

283
00:22:32,581 --> 00:22:33,415
Don't you

284
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:36,418
trust Father?

285
00:22:38,628 --> 00:22:40,881
I do know he's hiding something from us.

286
00:22:41,381 --> 00:22:42,424
Like about 3972.

287
00:22:43,717 --> 00:22:46,386
Father does everything
for a reason, Ho-ran.

288
00:22:46,470 --> 00:22:49,264
Yeah, I'm sure he does.

289
00:22:50,599 --> 00:22:52,309
But I'm not sure if that reason

290
00:22:52,809 --> 00:22:55,187
is for our good.

291
00:22:55,270 --> 00:22:58,231
Stop thinking useless thoughts
and go do your job.

292
00:22:58,940 --> 00:23:01,860
Because if we fail to find
the Child of Eternity…

293
00:23:04,488 --> 00:23:07,616
all that awaits us,
Father included, is death.

294
00:23:08,617 --> 00:23:11,161
Okay, I got it.

295
00:24:05,966 --> 00:24:06,967
My goodness!

296
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:12,138
-My congratulations!
-Oh my.

297
00:24:12,222 --> 00:24:13,932
Have a read before you go in!

298
00:24:14,015 --> 00:24:15,767
-Oh my!
-Congratulations!

299
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:17,686
-Go in now.
-She got a job?

300
00:24:17,769 --> 00:24:20,564
-Congratulations!
-Thank you.

301
00:24:22,274 --> 00:24:24,317
So do you think it can be restored?

302
00:24:24,401 --> 00:24:26,486
No, it doesn't seem likely.

303
00:24:27,821 --> 00:24:31,116
It wasn't just overwritten
but completely erased by a magnetic field.

304
00:24:32,492 --> 00:24:35,662
I spent a fortune installing
those security cameras or whatnot,

305
00:24:35,745 --> 00:24:37,038
but they're darn useless.

306
00:24:37,122 --> 00:24:39,708
One camera managed to capture something.

307
00:24:39,791 --> 00:24:40,792
What?

308
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:44,713
The camera out back.

309
00:25:06,443 --> 00:25:07,360
What is it?

310
00:25:09,029 --> 00:25:12,699
It's that woman.
The variant 3972 hangs out with.

311
00:25:18,705 --> 00:25:19,539
What should we do?

312
00:25:22,208 --> 00:25:23,084
Collect her.

313
00:25:37,265 --> 00:25:39,643
If this works, it'll be huge.

314
00:25:39,726 --> 00:25:43,855
The northern lights.
It'd be great if I could really go there.

315
00:25:45,607 --> 00:25:46,650
The northern lights.

316
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:49,027
How awesome would that be?

317
00:25:50,945 --> 00:25:52,322
Let's go. Yeah.

318
00:25:53,073 --> 00:25:53,948
Let's go!

319
00:25:57,118 --> 00:25:58,370
Guess not.

320
00:25:58,453 --> 00:26:00,038
Okay, focus.

321
00:26:02,957 --> 00:26:03,958
And I'm still here.

322
00:26:04,459 --> 00:26:05,710
Okay, focus now.

323
00:26:18,056 --> 00:26:18,890
Did you see that?

324
00:26:18,973 --> 00:26:20,725
What on earth happened

325
00:26:21,559 --> 00:26:22,977
to my Chae-ni just now?

326
00:26:24,187 --> 00:26:25,438
Did she just vanish?

327
00:26:26,981 --> 00:26:29,150
Did you succeed? Where did you go? Norway?

328
00:26:29,234 --> 00:26:30,193
Finland?

329
00:26:30,276 --> 00:26:31,820
Did you really see the aurora?

330
00:26:36,324 --> 00:26:37,158
I did.

331
00:26:37,242 --> 00:26:38,743
AURORA

332
00:26:39,244 --> 00:26:42,914
<i>Put a name tag on my chest…</i>

333
00:26:42,997 --> 00:26:44,040
I'm here, baby.

334
00:26:44,124 --> 00:26:45,250
Cheers!

335
00:26:48,044 --> 00:26:49,629
Deary me. Miss?

336
00:26:50,797 --> 00:26:52,924
No, don't go. Why are you leaving?

337
00:26:53,425 --> 00:26:54,759
Come again tomorrow.

338
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:56,386
She's cute.

339
00:27:00,598 --> 00:27:01,433
How pathetic.

340
00:27:01,516 --> 00:27:04,018
I'd expect nothing less from a half-wit.

341
00:27:04,102 --> 00:27:06,855
Cut her some slack. She half-succeeded.

342
00:27:06,938 --> 00:27:07,897
Well done, Chae-ni.

343
00:27:07,981 --> 00:27:10,275
Do you find this funny, Mr. Son?

344
00:27:10,775 --> 00:27:12,986
Would it be funny
if Cheong saw you get stuck?

345
00:27:13,069 --> 00:27:15,822
Hey, keep family out of this.

346
00:27:15,905 --> 00:27:18,742
Then stop slacking off and practice.

347
00:27:18,825 --> 00:27:22,162
I'm super scared that I'll end up
disappearing in front of Grandma.

348
00:27:22,245 --> 00:27:24,372
She'd probably keel over from shock.

349
00:27:24,873 --> 00:27:25,957
That's not all.

350
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:28,835
I'd be locked up forever
in the biggest hospital in Seoul.

351
00:27:29,335 --> 00:27:33,089
I'm more scared of Grandma finding out
than being carted off somewhere.

352
00:27:33,173 --> 00:27:35,133
I'm super desperate too.

353
00:27:35,633 --> 00:27:37,218
Do you know what my dream is?

354
00:27:37,761 --> 00:27:38,970
It's to be Uri Geller.

355
00:27:39,888 --> 00:27:41,055
Your dream

356
00:27:41,765 --> 00:27:43,099
is to be a con artist?

357
00:27:43,183 --> 00:27:44,934
You're so clueless.

358
00:27:45,435 --> 00:27:48,897
Uri Geller is a real psychic,
and he makes a ton of money.

359
00:27:51,232 --> 00:27:52,108
This.

360
00:27:52,901 --> 00:27:54,444
If I could gift one of these

361
00:27:54,527 --> 00:27:56,696
to each of Cheong's classmates,
I'd die happy.

362
00:27:58,865 --> 00:27:59,699
If I'm honest,

363
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,203
like Mr. Son,
I also have something I'd like to do.

364
00:28:03,286 --> 00:28:04,120
What?

365
00:28:04,621 --> 00:28:06,080
Well, thanks to you,

366
00:28:06,164 --> 00:28:09,042
I had a pretty easy time in high school,

367
00:28:09,667 --> 00:28:11,961
but middle school was pretty rough.

368
00:28:12,045 --> 00:28:15,131
I want to go and revisit every kid
who bullied me back then.

369
00:28:16,174 --> 00:28:18,843
Hey, Kang Ro-bin!

370
00:28:19,928 --> 00:28:21,971
Is the worm finally tuning?

371
00:28:22,055 --> 00:28:25,099
What would you do to them?
Hurt them? Get revenge?

372
00:28:25,183 --> 00:28:26,935
No.

373
00:28:28,144 --> 00:28:29,103
I want to brag.

374
00:28:30,313 --> 00:28:31,898
That I've become really strong.

375
00:28:32,565 --> 00:28:34,359
Typical Sappy Sap.

376
00:28:34,943 --> 00:28:37,612
Can't you just go on
a brutal, bloodstained revenge spree?

377
00:28:37,695 --> 00:28:39,739
A guy like me get revenge? No way.

378
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:42,200
Besides, in some ways,

379
00:28:42,283 --> 00:28:44,869
I sort of feel bad for my superpower.

380
00:28:45,370 --> 00:28:47,914
If it had gone to someone cooler,

381
00:28:47,997 --> 00:28:51,376
they would've used it in cool ways,
saved people, and all that.

382
00:28:51,876 --> 00:28:55,046
But it had to come
to someone useless like me.

383
00:28:55,129 --> 00:28:56,673
Now it's really useless.

384
00:28:58,258 --> 00:29:02,345
I recently saw the historical drama
<i>500 Years of the Joseon Dynasty</i>.

385
00:29:03,096 --> 00:29:04,472
They had these scapeghosts.

386
00:29:04,556 --> 00:29:05,890
<i>Scapegoat</i>, you mean.

387
00:29:05,974 --> 00:29:08,434
Anyway, they were basically goalies.

388
00:29:08,935 --> 00:29:12,397
They'd use their bodies
to block and absorb all the bad energy

389
00:29:12,897 --> 00:29:14,190
to protect the royal court.

390
00:29:14,274 --> 00:29:15,859
What's that got to do with me?

391
00:29:17,318 --> 00:29:20,405
Who else could handle the Royal Nightmare,

392
00:29:20,488 --> 00:29:21,739
Lady Trainwreck,

393
00:29:21,823 --> 00:29:24,409
and the curmudgeonly old lady
of Hearty House?

394
00:29:24,909 --> 00:29:26,703
Who would keep the peace in Haeseong?

395
00:29:29,706 --> 00:29:32,959
First, let's just try to figure out
how to use these abilities.

396
00:29:33,042 --> 00:29:36,504
He said we could avoid being carted off
and live normal, quiet lives.

397
00:29:36,588 --> 00:29:38,673
And once we get used to them,

398
00:29:39,716 --> 00:29:43,595
I'll get you some undies to wear
over your tights, like Superman.

399
00:29:44,095 --> 00:29:46,681
Really? And I get to pick out the design?

400
00:29:46,764 --> 00:29:47,849
I dare you.

401
00:29:52,061 --> 00:29:52,979
Hello?

402
00:29:53,897 --> 00:29:54,731
Hey, Grandma.

403
00:29:55,231 --> 00:29:57,775
I'm busy with my public duties.
What is it now?

404
00:29:59,736 --> 00:30:00,653
Hello?

405
00:30:02,405 --> 00:30:03,489
Hello? Grandma?

406
00:30:03,573 --> 00:30:05,658
Just tell me where you are.

407
00:30:05,742 --> 00:30:08,119
Do your public duties later
and come home now.

408
00:30:08,661 --> 00:30:09,537
Never mind.

409
00:30:09,621 --> 00:30:11,539
I'll pick you up. Where are you now?

410
00:30:11,623 --> 00:30:12,457
<i>Hello?</i>

411
00:30:12,957 --> 00:30:14,334
<i>-Grandma.</i>
-Hello?

412
00:30:14,417 --> 00:30:15,835
<i>-I can hear--</i>
-Eunie?

413
00:30:15,919 --> 00:30:17,629
<i>-Yes, Grandma--</i>
-Eunie!

414
00:30:18,129 --> 00:30:18,963
<i>Hello?</i>

415
00:30:19,547 --> 00:30:21,341
<i>-Hello? Grandma!</i>
-Where are you?

416
00:30:23,384 --> 00:30:24,761
Hey, Gunie.

417
00:30:24,844 --> 00:30:27,889
Hurry back to the office
and find out where Eun Chae-ni is.

418
00:30:27,972 --> 00:30:28,806
Sorry?

419
00:30:29,641 --> 00:30:31,059
Right, okay.

420
00:30:34,395 --> 00:30:35,271
But, Ms. Kim,

421
00:30:36,314 --> 00:30:37,774
I guess you weren't aware

422
00:30:37,857 --> 00:30:40,526
that Eun Chae-ni had such an ability.

423
00:30:46,366 --> 00:30:47,367
Hello?

424
00:30:48,743 --> 00:30:50,244
Hey, Jun-mo.

425
00:30:53,998 --> 00:30:55,500
About Chae-ni.

426
00:30:55,583 --> 00:30:58,711
Looks like she's working hard
at the Civil Complaints Office.

427
00:31:00,672 --> 00:31:03,007
She hasn't budged an inch from City Hall.

428
00:31:03,967 --> 00:31:05,093
I see.

429
00:31:06,803 --> 00:31:08,096
And you're doing good?

430
00:31:08,179 --> 00:31:09,639
Of course.

431
00:31:10,139 --> 00:31:12,850
You'll be the first to know
if anything happens, Grandma.

432
00:31:15,144 --> 00:31:16,104
That's it.

433
00:31:16,771 --> 00:31:19,857
Jun-mo has always called me Grandma.

434
00:31:20,441 --> 00:31:23,277
He's never called me "Ms. Kim."

435
00:31:26,739 --> 00:31:28,741
Damn, you caught me.

436
00:31:29,909 --> 00:31:32,620
It's always the little details
that give me away.

437
00:31:56,185 --> 00:31:57,520
Whose daughter are you?

438
00:31:57,603 --> 00:31:59,272
Dr. Ha Won-do.

439
00:31:59,355 --> 00:32:00,565
He's my father.

440
00:32:01,482 --> 00:32:02,316
You

441
00:32:03,693 --> 00:32:05,611
call that man your father?

442
00:32:05,695 --> 00:32:07,905
He's the only one who took us in.

443
00:32:08,698 --> 00:32:09,949
I guess I'm to blame.

444
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,952
I failed to take care of you all.

445
00:32:16,372 --> 00:32:18,916
Don't say things you don't mean.

446
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:21,544
We know you only saved the kids
without abilities.

447
00:32:26,215 --> 00:32:28,885
You were afraid of the world
finding out we existed,

448
00:32:29,385 --> 00:32:30,344
weren't you?

449
00:32:32,055 --> 00:32:34,390
That's why you didn't save
the Wunderkinder.

450
00:32:34,474 --> 00:32:37,935
You just left us to die
in that burning lab.

451
00:32:39,562 --> 00:32:41,147
Did Ha Won-do tell you that?

452
00:32:41,981 --> 00:32:43,232
Child, that's not true.

453
00:32:43,316 --> 00:32:45,276
You only took the Child of Eternity.

454
00:32:47,737 --> 00:32:52,325
You guys only took the Child of Eternity,
who you needed, and as for the rest of us…

455
00:32:55,203 --> 00:32:56,204
you abandoned us.

456
00:32:57,789 --> 00:32:58,998
So that's it.

457
00:32:59,999 --> 00:33:01,084
The reason you're here.

458
00:33:04,712 --> 00:33:05,671
Where are they now?

459
00:33:05,755 --> 00:33:06,923
The child's dead.

460
00:33:08,508 --> 00:33:12,345
My sister's ability may not have worked
on you, but don't underestimate mine.

461
00:33:12,887 --> 00:33:16,307
I can make you experience

462
00:33:17,141 --> 00:33:18,101
hell on earth.

463
00:33:28,569 --> 00:33:29,529
Let me ask.

464
00:33:30,947 --> 00:33:33,658
Do I look like I'm in a good place to you?

465
00:33:36,494 --> 00:33:39,664
After losing all those precious children,

466
00:33:40,331 --> 00:33:44,293
my own child was the one
who had to pay for that sin, not me.

467
00:33:49,090 --> 00:33:50,967
You needn't bother.

468
00:33:51,968 --> 00:33:53,553
The past 20 years

469
00:33:54,053 --> 00:33:56,013
have already been hell on earth.

470
00:33:58,307 --> 00:34:00,268
Hello, we're here.

471
00:34:00,351 --> 00:34:02,019
-Hello.
-Please sit.

472
00:34:02,103 --> 00:34:04,355
-Welcome.
-Yes, hello.

473
00:34:04,438 --> 00:34:06,566
-Welcome.
-Whatever you want to eat.

474
00:34:07,108 --> 00:34:09,277
-Welcome.
-What should we eat?

475
00:34:13,823 --> 00:34:16,117
If that child really is dead,

476
00:34:17,535 --> 00:34:18,911
you'd better find the body.

477
00:34:20,955 --> 00:34:24,834
Or I'll show you true hell on earth.

478
00:34:32,091 --> 00:34:33,050
Did you hear that?

479
00:34:34,302 --> 00:34:35,261
<i>You'd better go</i>

480
00:34:36,304 --> 00:34:38,890
<i>and find Chae-ni right now, Jun-mo.</i>

481
00:34:42,727 --> 00:34:49,358
<i>It is his will</i>

482
00:34:49,442 --> 00:34:55,114
<i>Forgive us our sins</i>

483
00:34:55,656 --> 00:35:02,079
<i>I will give my life</i>

484
00:35:02,163 --> 00:35:07,418
<i>To be saved</i>

485
00:35:08,377 --> 00:35:14,300
<i>A place where</i>

486
00:35:14,383 --> 00:35:19,931
<i>An endless paradise unfolds</i>

487
00:35:20,431 --> 00:35:26,312
<i>I will go to him</i>

488
00:35:28,731 --> 00:35:30,441
Hey, look!

489
00:35:30,983 --> 00:35:34,237
Are we even sure there are rules?
I have no clue.

490
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:37,031
Just sticking and unsticking willy-nilly.

491
00:35:37,114 --> 00:35:38,366
And the body part too.

492
00:35:39,075 --> 00:35:42,286
Sometimes it's my butt. Sometimes my arm.
It's completely random.

493
00:35:43,079 --> 00:35:45,748
There must be some kind of rule.
Think harder.

494
00:35:49,168 --> 00:35:50,628
You should think <i>really </i>hard.

495
00:35:50,711 --> 00:35:53,756
Don't you have the most to gain?
You'd have the strength of a tiger.

496
00:35:56,259 --> 00:35:57,093
Tears?

497
00:35:58,761 --> 00:36:00,012
I think I was crying.

498
00:36:06,352 --> 00:36:07,270
Tears.

499
00:36:07,353 --> 00:36:08,854
-He's crying.
-Try it now!

500
00:36:08,938 --> 00:36:10,106
Okay, straight punch.

501
00:36:10,189 --> 00:36:11,274
Okay, hi-yah!

502
00:36:11,357 --> 00:36:12,275
Okay.

503
00:36:13,693 --> 00:36:14,527
It didn't work?

504
00:36:15,945 --> 00:36:16,821
Hey, more tears.

505
00:36:16,904 --> 00:36:17,822
Let's try again.

506
00:36:17,905 --> 00:36:19,532
Put your back into it!

507
00:36:19,615 --> 00:36:20,449
Okay.

508
00:36:20,950 --> 00:36:21,867
Karate chop.

509
00:36:21,951 --> 00:36:23,869
-Hi-yah!
-Hi-yah!

510
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:27,581
Go again. Hi-yah!

511
00:36:29,166 --> 00:36:30,459
I can't do it.

512
00:36:30,543 --> 00:36:32,962
Just hit it. What's a few broken fingers?

513
00:36:33,045 --> 00:36:33,921
It hurts.

514
00:36:34,005 --> 00:36:35,756
Don't just stand like this. Do it!

515
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,967
Okay, just once. Okay, go!

516
00:36:38,050 --> 00:36:39,135
One, two.

517
00:36:39,677 --> 00:36:40,803
It hurts too much.

518
00:36:42,305 --> 00:36:43,973
Your tears are drying up.

519
00:36:44,056 --> 00:36:44,932
Go again?

520
00:36:45,016 --> 00:36:45,850
Hold on.

521
00:36:46,392 --> 00:36:47,518
It hurts.

522
00:36:48,978 --> 00:36:51,314
Hold your horses.

523
00:36:51,397 --> 00:36:54,567
I think I'm onto something.

524
00:36:55,067 --> 00:36:55,901
<i>Run!</i>

525
00:37:04,243 --> 00:37:06,037
Do I need to be out of breath?

526
00:37:07,872 --> 00:37:09,373
One, two!

527
00:37:10,082 --> 00:37:12,376
Hey, you punk! Why'd you hit me…

528
00:37:15,546 --> 00:37:17,798
Okay. Karate chop!

529
00:37:28,100 --> 00:37:29,518
I'll see you later.

530
00:37:33,439 --> 00:37:35,649
This is the end of my patrol area.

531
00:37:35,733 --> 00:37:37,401
This field is the last stop.

532
00:37:37,485 --> 00:37:38,319
I see.

533
00:37:40,196 --> 00:37:42,531
So this will be the last stop.

534
00:37:44,825 --> 00:37:46,327
Thank you for your help.

535
00:37:46,410 --> 00:37:48,621
I think I can take it from here.

536
00:37:48,704 --> 00:37:49,622
That's all right.

537
00:37:49,705 --> 00:37:53,084
I was told that we should see
the clean-up through to the end.

538
00:37:54,126 --> 00:37:55,044
Who said that?

539
00:37:55,127 --> 00:37:58,756
Who else?
Our very own shepherd, Kim Pal-ho.

540
00:38:01,967 --> 00:38:04,512
And it seems you have blind faith
in your shepherd.

541
00:38:05,888 --> 00:38:06,722
No.

542
00:38:07,431 --> 00:38:09,392
To believe or not to believe

543
00:38:09,475 --> 00:38:12,186
involves human will, does it not?

544
00:38:12,269 --> 00:38:15,231
We do not believe. We know.

545
00:38:17,566 --> 00:38:20,027
We are aware of the fact

546
00:38:20,528 --> 00:38:22,363
that the apocalypse is near.

547
00:38:23,906 --> 00:38:25,908
"The apocalypse will come."

548
00:38:25,991 --> 00:38:28,452
"There is no escaping that fact."

549
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:33,374
"Everyone dies.
There is no escaping that fact."

550
00:38:33,958 --> 00:38:35,000
How are they different?

551
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,169
The difference

552
00:38:37,253 --> 00:38:42,133
is that our shepherd knows when, where,
and how the apocalypse will happen.

553
00:38:42,216 --> 00:38:44,593
What's the point of
knowing about the apocalypse

554
00:38:45,094 --> 00:38:46,595
if you can't avoid it?

555
00:38:47,847 --> 00:38:50,057
That's right. It cannot be avoided.

556
00:38:50,141 --> 00:38:52,017
Not by foolish humans.

557
00:38:52,101 --> 00:38:55,646
But the Church of Eternal Salvation
is different.

558
00:38:55,729 --> 00:38:57,064
We <i>can </i>be saved.

559
00:39:00,776 --> 00:39:04,155
We have witnessed miracles
with our own two eyes.

560
00:39:04,238 --> 00:39:06,073
And we know that such miracles

561
00:39:06,615 --> 00:39:10,035
will be granted to us
at the moment of the apocalypse.

562
00:39:12,163 --> 00:39:14,915
Whatever you saw wasn't a miracle, but…

563
00:39:34,059 --> 00:39:35,936
Lord, are you with us?

564
00:39:37,271 --> 00:39:39,440
My Lord!

565
00:39:41,066 --> 00:39:43,694
My Lord! Please forgive us our sins.

566
00:39:43,777 --> 00:39:44,945
Please save us.

567
00:39:45,029 --> 00:39:49,074
Save all our believers
in the midst of the apocalypse!

568
00:39:49,575 --> 00:39:50,534
Are you here?

569
00:39:50,618 --> 00:39:52,161
Please forgive my sins.

570
00:39:52,244 --> 00:39:56,665
I am ready to give my life for you!

571
00:39:59,251 --> 00:40:01,879
Shepherd Kim Pal-ho asked me
to pass on a message.

572
00:40:01,962 --> 00:40:04,924
Number 3972,
your apocalypse shall take place

573
00:40:05,007 --> 00:40:06,467
right here, today,

574
00:40:06,550 --> 00:40:08,469
and there shall be no mercy.

575
00:41:40,894 --> 00:41:44,398
You laughed earlier, didn't you?
When he said "Shepherd Kim Pal-ho."

576
00:41:47,026 --> 00:41:48,402
What are you talking about?

577
00:41:48,902 --> 00:41:49,820
You crazy bastard!

578
00:42:01,832 --> 00:42:05,336
Didn't you know that disbelief
in the shepherd gets you a ticket to hell?

579
00:42:16,013 --> 00:42:17,973
Hey, Kang Ro-bin, you bastard!

580
00:42:18,474 --> 00:42:20,309
How dare you throw an adult up here!

581
00:42:20,976 --> 00:42:24,480
I did throw you, but you were the one
who got yourself stuck up there.

582
00:42:24,563 --> 00:42:25,522
Why, you…

583
00:42:26,607 --> 00:42:28,525
I ran so hard that I'm out of breath,

584
00:42:28,609 --> 00:42:30,611
so why isn't my heart racing?

585
00:42:30,694 --> 00:42:31,570
This is weird.

586
00:42:33,405 --> 00:42:35,282
Maybe you have to decide where to go.

587
00:42:35,366 --> 00:42:37,743
But there's nowhere
I want to go right now.

588
00:42:39,703 --> 00:42:43,540
I have to figure this out
so I can tell Master and show off.

589
00:42:47,419 --> 00:42:50,130
I'm just dying to show off!

590
00:42:52,257 --> 00:42:53,467
Chae-ni!

591
00:42:56,762 --> 00:42:57,930
No matter what,

592
00:42:59,181 --> 00:43:00,891
I will become Uri Geller.

593
00:43:02,101 --> 00:43:04,687
But why won't I get off?

594
00:43:11,610 --> 00:43:12,945
Pretty awesome!

595
00:43:13,612 --> 00:43:17,032
Hey, Master! I did it.

596
00:43:17,116 --> 00:43:20,035
I thought hard and focused like you said,
and I ended up--

597
00:43:25,666 --> 00:43:26,709
Run.

598
00:43:35,759 --> 00:43:37,928
-What the heck?
-Eun Chae-ni!

599
00:43:38,595 --> 00:43:40,097
Where's Master?

600
00:43:40,180 --> 00:43:41,432
It's just you. What is it?

601
00:43:43,225 --> 00:43:45,185
Master is in danger!

602
00:43:45,269 --> 00:43:47,980
You have to give
the who, what, when, where, why, and how.

603
00:43:48,063 --> 00:43:50,399
You can't just say he's in danger
and expect us to…

604
00:43:50,482 --> 00:43:52,025
Who am I even talking to?

605
00:43:52,526 --> 00:43:54,778
All the blood in my body
is rushing to my head.

606
00:43:54,862 --> 00:43:55,988
Someone get me down.

607
00:43:58,282 --> 00:43:59,867
What?

608
00:44:02,995 --> 00:44:04,246
What is that?

609
00:44:04,329 --> 00:44:05,581
Chae-ni! No!

610
00:44:06,123 --> 00:44:07,166
Get up.

611
00:44:10,836 --> 00:44:12,087
Chae-ni!

612
00:44:14,298 --> 00:44:16,300
Chae-ni!

613
00:44:17,426 --> 00:44:18,469
Master!

614
00:44:24,224 --> 00:44:25,476
Master.

615
00:44:27,352 --> 00:44:29,188
Now you've brought Kang Ro-bin too?

616
00:44:29,271 --> 00:44:30,105
Go back, now!

617
00:44:30,189 --> 00:44:31,774
We have to go together!

618
00:44:32,816 --> 00:44:33,650
Hey, Kang Ro-bin!

619
00:44:40,491 --> 00:44:41,575
Oh no!

620
00:44:41,658 --> 00:44:42,576
Focus.

621
00:44:48,332 --> 00:44:49,208
What are you doing?

622
00:44:49,291 --> 00:44:52,044
Hey, don't talk to me!
Why isn't it working?

623
00:44:52,628 --> 00:44:53,462
Let's go!

624
00:45:23,617 --> 00:45:25,285
What is this?

625
00:45:27,162 --> 00:45:28,163
He's a Wunderkinder.

626
00:45:40,092 --> 00:45:40,968
Hurry, go back.

627
00:45:41,051 --> 00:45:44,137
I'm dying to go back too.

628
00:45:46,139 --> 00:45:47,683
Chae-ni, what do we do?

629
00:45:47,766 --> 00:45:49,852
It looks like we're going to die here!

630
00:45:49,935 --> 00:45:51,937
Get off me and stop whining!

631
00:45:52,020 --> 00:45:53,063
Stop freeloading,

632
00:45:53,146 --> 00:45:56,817
and think of something
that'll actually help us yourself!

633
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,286
No!

634
00:47:43,799 --> 00:47:46,218
Chae-ni! Did you see that?

635
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:47,886
I just…

636
00:47:49,304 --> 00:47:50,597
Chae-ni!

637
00:47:51,765 --> 00:47:52,849
Where did Chae-ni…

638
00:47:53,475 --> 00:47:54,309
Chae-ni!

639
00:47:56,144 --> 00:47:57,187
Chae-ni!

640
00:48:21,253 --> 00:48:22,337
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

641
00:48:23,839 --> 00:48:24,715
Ms. Chae-ni!

642
00:48:25,674 --> 00:48:26,925
Are you okay?

643
00:48:27,426 --> 00:48:28,427
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

644
00:48:32,639 --> 00:48:33,932
This time,

645
00:48:35,267 --> 00:48:37,519
I actually did it.

646
00:48:40,939 --> 00:48:43,692
It's the northern lights.

647
00:49:01,585 --> 00:49:03,170
It's my first time

648
00:49:04,296 --> 00:49:06,548
being outside of Haeseong.

649
00:49:16,850 --> 00:49:18,351
It's beautiful.

650
00:49:30,614 --> 00:49:31,448
Hey.

651
00:49:32,115 --> 00:49:32,949
Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

652
00:49:34,117 --> 00:49:34,951
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

653
00:49:35,452 --> 00:49:36,411
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

654
00:49:54,429 --> 00:49:56,723
Chae-ni!

655
00:49:57,224 --> 00:49:58,683
Eun Chae-ni!

656
00:49:59,184 --> 00:50:02,354
How could you leave me here all alone?

657
00:50:06,650 --> 00:50:08,068
You scared me.

658
00:50:08,568 --> 00:50:10,737
You could've made some noise or something.

659
00:50:10,821 --> 00:50:11,988
And who are you?

660
00:50:13,281 --> 00:50:14,199
Another defective?

661
00:50:16,118 --> 00:50:17,035
Me?

662
00:50:17,619 --> 00:50:18,870
Who said I defected?

663
00:50:23,166 --> 00:50:27,671
If you're a Wunderkinder, that means
you also have a superpower, doesn't it?

664
00:50:33,093 --> 00:50:34,678
Why are you doing that?

665
00:51:13,550 --> 00:51:14,676
What are you doing?

666
00:51:16,970 --> 00:51:17,888
What are you?

667
00:51:18,471 --> 00:51:19,556
I'm Kang Ro-bin.

668
00:51:22,142 --> 00:51:24,477
Wait, why do you keep clapping?

669
00:51:28,565 --> 00:51:29,774
Should I be copying him?

670
00:51:32,110 --> 00:51:32,944
Boom pow?

671
00:51:35,614 --> 00:51:36,781
Boom boom pow!

672
00:51:39,659 --> 00:51:41,119
Boom boom pow!

673
00:51:41,203 --> 00:51:42,787
Boom boom pow!

674
00:51:42,871 --> 00:51:44,873
Boom boom pow!

675
00:51:44,956 --> 00:51:47,667
Boom boom pow! Is this it? Boom boom pow!

676
00:51:49,085 --> 00:51:50,253
Pow!

677
00:51:52,797 --> 00:51:54,424
This is it, right? Boom boom pow!

678
00:51:54,507 --> 00:51:56,343
Boom boom pow!

679
00:51:56,426 --> 00:51:57,510
Ha, ha, pow!

680
00:51:59,512 --> 00:52:04,142
<i>I recently saw the historical drama</i>
500 Years of the Joseon Dynasty.

681
00:52:04,768 --> 00:52:06,561
<i>They had scapeghosts.</i>

682
00:52:07,062 --> 00:52:08,813
Scapegoat<i>, you mean.</i>

683
00:52:08,897 --> 00:52:11,233
<i>Anyway, they were basically goalies.</i>

684
00:52:11,983 --> 00:52:15,820
<i>They'd use their bodies</i>
<i>to block and absorb all the bad energy</i>

685
00:52:15,904 --> 00:52:17,697
<i>to protect the royal court.</i>

686
00:52:36,841 --> 00:52:38,593
Peek-a-boo! Wait, not peek-a-boo.

687
00:52:38,677 --> 00:52:41,137
First of all,
I'm glad you're not too surprised.

688
00:52:41,221 --> 00:52:42,514
Deary me, this is…

689
00:52:42,597 --> 00:52:45,016
Right, I am Son Gyeong--

690
00:52:48,478 --> 00:52:49,938
Just a second.

691
00:52:50,480 --> 00:52:51,690
My head's spinning.

692
00:52:54,317 --> 00:52:55,193
I'm good now.

693
00:52:56,611 --> 00:52:59,447
You were… stuck up there?

694
00:53:00,657 --> 00:53:03,201
No. What do you mean "stuck"?

695
00:53:03,785 --> 00:53:06,496
I performed some magic tricks
for a talent show,

696
00:53:06,579 --> 00:53:07,706
and the kids…

697
00:53:08,665 --> 00:53:10,500
I wonder where the kids went…

698
00:53:13,461 --> 00:53:14,337
Not again…

699
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:21,177
Mister, what are you doing right now?

700
00:53:23,638 --> 00:53:24,681
Hold on.

701
00:53:27,183 --> 00:53:28,935
I just…

702
00:53:32,063 --> 00:53:35,066
By the way, where is Chae-ni right now?

703
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:08,965
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

